
[1]pitiful

   PIT'IFUL, a. [See Pity.] Full of pity; tender; compassionate; having a
   heart to feel sorrow and sympathy for the distressed. James 5. 1 Pet.3.
   [This is the proper sense of the word.]

   1. Miserable; moving compassion; as a sight most pitiful; a pitiful
   condition.

   2. To be pitied for its littleness or meanness; paltry; contemptible;
   despicable.

   That's villainous, and shows a most pitiful ambition in the fool that
   uses it.

   3. Very small; insignificant.
